08/09/2003
ZAGREB, Croatia -- The ruling Social Democratic Party (SDP) formally launched its campaign for the November parliamentary elections on Monday (8 September). 
At a weekend meeting with party officials in Zagreb, Prime Minister Ivica Racan, who also leads SDP, called on members to show what "SDP has done for Zagreb and Croatia". 
He stressed progress achieved towards Euro-Atlantic integration. 
(HINA, BBC - 06/09/03)
